---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import Callout from '../components/Callout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/url';

const repo = 'https://github.com/maheshpchandran/EtiKette';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contribute"
  description="How to add or correct a dining-etiquette guide on EtiKette. No coding required — just Markdown."
>
  <div class="container prose">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: withBase('/') }, { label: 'Contribute' }]} />
    <h1>Contribute</h1>
    <p>
      EtiKette grows through contributions from people who know their region’s
      food culture. You don’t need to be a developer — every guide is a plain
      Markdown file.
    </p>

    <h2>Three ways to help</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fix or refine a detail</strong> on an existing page.</li>
      <li><strong>Add a topic</strong> to a region that’s already started.</li>
      <li><strong>Add a whole new region</strong> (see the steps in the repository’s <code>CONTRIBUTING.md</code>).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How a page is written</h2>
    <p>Each topic lives at <code>src/content/regions/&lt;region&gt;/&lt;topic&gt;.md</code>
      and starts with a small block of frontmatter, then plain Markdown:</p>

    <pre><code>---
title: The Sadya
summary: How a Kerala feast is laid out on a banana leaf and eaten in courses.
order: 1
icon: "🍛"
sources:
  - label: "Sadya — Wikipedia"
    url: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sadya
lastUpdated: 2026-05-25
---

Write the guide here in normal Markdown.

:::hygiene
Flag a health risk and offer a safer alternative like this.
:::</code></pre>

    <Callout type="tip" title="Callouts in Markdown">
      <p>Wrap a paragraph in <code>:::tip</code>, <code>:::hygiene</code>,
        <code>:::tradition</code>, or <code>:::variation</code> (closed with
        <code>:::</code>) to get a styled callout — no components to import.</p>
    </Callout>

    <h2>House style</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Describe, don’t prescribe.</strong> Record what people do; avoid “you must”.</li>
      <li><strong>Name the variation.</strong> Say when a custom differs by community, faith, or family.</li>
      <li><strong>Cite where you can.</strong> Add references to the <code>sources</code> list.</li>
      <li><strong>Be respectful about hygiene.</strong> Explain the risk and a kinder, safer option — never mock.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Submitting</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Fork the repository and create a branch.</li>
      <li>Add or edit the Markdown file(s). Run <code>npm run dev</code> to preview locally.</li>
      <li>Open a pull request describing your change and any sources.</li>
    </ol>

    <p style="margin-top:1.5rem">
      <a class="btn" href={repo}>Open the repository on GitHub</a>
      &nbsp;
      <a class="btn secondary" href={`${repo}/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md`}>Read CONTRIBUTING.md</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
